# Blocks Field Enhancements

## Overview

Two UX improvements to the `blocks` field type in `packages/ui/src/fields/Blocks/`:

1. **Single-block auto-add** ‚Äì when a blocks field has exactly one available block type, clicking "Add" immediately inserts it without opening the block selection drawer.
2. **Fast-add dropdown** ‚Äì when a blocks field has multiple block types, a chevron dropdown button appears next to the "Add" button, listing all available blocks for one-click adding.

## Architecture

### Component hierarchy (add-block flow)

```
BlocksField (index.tsx)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ [single block]  ‚Üí  <button onClick={addRow(slug)}>    ‚Üê direct add, no drawer
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ [multi block]   ‚Üí  <div.add-button-group>
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <DrawerToggler>  ‚Üí  opens BlocksDrawer           ‚Üê original full drawer
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <Popup>          ‚Üí  fast-add dropdown             ‚Üê new quick menu
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ BlocksDrawer         ‚Üí  Drawer > BlockSelector        ‚Üê untouched

RowActions (RowActions.tsx)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ArrayAction.addRow callback
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ [single block]  ‚Üí  addRow(index, slug) directly   ‚Üê skip drawer
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [multi block]   ‚Üí  openModal(drawerSlug)          ‚Üê original behavior
```

### Key decision point

The branch is `clientBlocksAfterFilter.length === 1`. This array already accounts for `blockReferences`, `blocksMap` resolution, and `filterOptions` ‚Äì so the check is always against the final set of blocks the user can actually choose from.

## Changed files

### `packages/ui/src/fields/Blocks/index.tsx`

The bottom section that renders the "Add" button was refactored from a single `DrawerToggler` ‚Üí `BlocksDrawer` pair into a conditional:

```tsx
{clientBlocksAfterFilter.length === 1 ? (
  // Single block: plain <button> that calls addRow() directly
  <button onClick={() => addRow(rows.length, slug)}>
    <Button icon="plus" ...>{label}</Button>
  </button>
) : (
  // Multiple blocks: original DrawerToggler + new Popup dropdown
  <div className="blocks-field__add-button-group">
    <DrawerToggler slug={drawerSlug}>
      <Button icon="plus" ...>{label}</Button>
    </DrawerToggler>
    <Popup
      button={<ChevronIcon />}
      render={({ close }) => (
        <PopupList.ButtonGroup>
          {clientBlocksAfterFilter.map(block => (
            <PopupList.Button onClick={() => { addRow(rows.length, block.slug); close() }}>
              {block.labels.singular}
            </PopupList.Button>
          ))}
        </PopupList.ButtonGroup>
      )}
    />
  </div>
)}
```

New imports added: `Popup`, `PopupList`, `ChevronIcon`.

The `BlocksDrawer` is always rendered (even for multi-block) because the main "Add" button still opens the full drawer with thumbnails and search.

### `packages/ui/src/fields/Blocks/RowActions.tsx`

The `ArrayAction.addRow` callback (triggered from the "..." row menu ‚Üí "Add Below") was changed to check `hasSingleBlock`:

```tsx
const hasSingleBlock = blocks.length === 1

// In ArrayAction.addRow:
if (hasSingleBlock) {
  void addRow(index, blocks[0].slug)   // direct add
} else {
  setIndexToAdd(index)
  openModal(drawerSlug)                 // open drawer as before
}
```

No changes to `BlocksDrawer` or `BlockSelector` ‚Äì those remain untouched.

### `packages/ui/src/fields/Blocks/index.scss`

New CSS classes added:

| Class | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `__add-button-group` | Flex row containing the DrawerToggler + Popup chevron side by side |
| `__fast-add` | Wrapper for the Popup component |
| `__fast-add-button` | Chevron trigger button styling (transparent, icon-sized, hover color) |

Also added `cursor: pointer` to `__drawer-toggler` (was missing for the new `<button>` element in single-block mode).

## Reused UI primitives

- **`Popup` + `PopupList`** (`elements/Popup/`) ‚Äì the same portal-based popup used in `ArrayAction` and other dropdowns throughout the admin UI. Handles positioning, click-outside-close, keyboard nav, and caret.
- **`ChevronIcon`** (`icons/Chevron/`) ‚Äì the standard chevron SVG, defaults to pointing down.
- **`DrawerToggler` + `BlocksDrawer`** ‚Äì unchanged, still used for the full visual drawer in multi-block mode.

## Edge cases handled

- **`blockReferences` vs `blocks`**: both paths resolve through `clientBlocksAfterFilter`, so the single-block check works regardless of how blocks are configured.
- **`filterOptions`**: if server-side `filterOptions` narrows the available blocks to 1, the auto-add kicks in even if the field config originally defined multiple blocks.
- **`readOnly` / `disabled`**: both the direct-add button and the fast-add popup respect these flags.
- **`maxRows`**: the entire add section is gated behind `!hasMaxRows`, so neither feature renders when the row limit is reached.
- **String blocks**: the code handles `ClientBlock | string` via `typeof _block === 'string' ? config.blocksMap[_block] : _block`.

## How to test

Add a blocks field with exactly 1 block to see auto-add, or 2+ blocks to see the fast-add dropdown. The `test/_community/collections/Posts/index.ts` config has example fields for both:

```ts
// Single block ‚Äì auto-add
{ name: 'singleBlockLayout', type: 'blocks', blocks: [{ slug: 'cta', ... }] }

// Multiple blocks ‚Äì fast-add dropdown
{ name: 'multiBlockLayout', type: 'blocks', blocks: [
  { slug: 'hero', ... },
  { slug: 'textContent', ... },
  { slug: 'imageGallery', ... },
] }
```

Run `pnpm run dev` and navigate to a Post edit page to see both fields.
